  <info>
    <title>Update strategy of desktop components</title><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
    <!--add author's email address-->
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
       In general, desktop components follow the balanced lifecycle of their packages. 
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    The &slea; 16 desktop environment provides the following components:
  </para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>GNOME desktop</term>
      <listitem>
<para>
The minimum version is <emphasis>48.0</emphasis>. The exact version must be determined before the
end of beta releases.
</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>GStreamer, PipeWire and Flatpak</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
These components are updated to the latest stable branch version at the last beta release.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Firefox</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          The minimum version is <emphasis>140.3</emphasis>. The update strategy follows the ESR update lifecycle.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>WebKit</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          The minimum version is <emphasis>2.46</emphasis>. WebKit has a periodic update cycle
          determined by critical CVEs. The component is updated but not backported.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>BRLTTY</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
The accessibility tools are at the latest upstream stable versions in the 16.0. Only bug fixes will
happen in this minor release.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>QT</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
The Qt 6 is delivered. The initial version is Qt 6.9.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>KDE</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
Not a standard &sle; delivery; available only in PackageHub 16. 
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</topic>
